h3. Issue Summary

Unable to edit "remaining Estimate" for the issue using the Rest API

h3. Steps to Reproduce

1. Change _Time display_ format from _Pretty_ to either _Hours_ or _Days_ 
 
2. Change the field using REST
 
3. Reference curl command:
{code:java}
 curl --request PUT \
  --url 'https://instance.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/issuekey' \
  --user 'ssingh7@atlassian.com:APItoken' \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
    "update": 
    {
        "timetracking": 
        [
            {
                "edit": {
                     "remainingEstimate": "0m"
                }
            }
        ]
    }
}'
{code}
 - You will get the following error:


h3. Expected Results

RemainingEstimate should get updated to 0m

h3. Actual Results

It is noticed that when the Original Estimate is a single digit after the decimal, we are able to set the remaining estimate but with 2 digits after the decimal, getting the error about the invalid value of the original estimate.


{code:java}
Error:
{"timetracking_originalestimate":"Specify a valid value
for Original estimate"}}
{code}

h3. Workaround

As a workaround, please change the _Time display_ format configuration to Pretty.
 !Screenshot 2021-10-21 at 1.01.14 PM.png|thumbnail!

{{Currently workratio is rounded down. This causes the problem that an issue which workratio is 100.4% is not shown for the JQL like the following.}}
{{* workratio > 100}}

It would be great Jira has the ability to calculate Workratio with decimal values.
